Description: myEHR is a healthcare technology company with the mission of transforming how electronic health records (EHRs) are transferred.
Full Description: Today, between 80–90% of all electronic health records are stored electronically, living on over 1700 unique EHR systems. Because of HIPAA, a set of rules and regulations that define how EHR’s should be transferred, none of these systems can communicate with each other seamlessly, and as a consequence most medical records are largely faxed from one provider to another.  This is a huge problem–providers have to spend time outlining faxed records, which in turn leads to the possibility of mistakes being made in the transfer process. Our solution has 3 parts.  First, we facilitate medical record transfers through our secure HIPAA–compliant blockchain system. Then, we allow for patients to give consent to transfer their medical record through our intuitive and easy to use patient account where they can manage and accept requests. Finally, we streamline the request process for providers by automating the patient medical record request system.  This saves the provider time, money, and gives them the ease of mind that the patient's health record smoothly and securely transfers into their system. No more faxing, no more cases of malpractice due to manual data entry, just one simple to use software package that smoothly integrates into the providers workflow.

Description: Make N Mod is a learning, design, and creation facility combined with a business incubator.
Full Description: Make N Mod is a coming design and creation facility combined with a business incubator to be launched in the coming year. We are dedicated to providing inventors, creators, and entrepreneurs with quality equipment and materials, excellent service, and furnishing a fun, clean, enjoyable atmosphere at an acceptable price. We will maintain a friendly creative work environment that respects diversity, ideas, and hard work. The timing is right for starting this new venture. The revolution of a new industry is upon us. The area of personal design and fabrication is expanding quickly as technologies advance and more cost effective equipment and materials have come in to the market. Many makers and entrepreneurs across the nation still can not afford even just a few of the necessary tools to meet their needs while almost none can afford the full suite of fabrication software, hardware, and equipment. We aim to provide them with access to a full set of the most relevant and up to date means to create at a fraction of the cost of ownership all while allowing them to run their very business out of our facilities. Joe Higgs, the founder, has worked in software design, hardware, networking, and systems administration for both government and non-government contractors for 20 years, has owned his own small business doing home automation and theater, and he has been a DIY-er and inventor since childhood. He has earned the respect of his colleagues through hard work, dedication, and a determined and positive attitude. Joe and his team have what it takes to make this venture extremely successful. Make N Mod will exceed the general expectation and grow a large, satisfied, and loyal customer base. For the convenience of our customers, Make N Mod will offer memberships and fee-based accessibility to computers with design software, prototyping equipment, hobby and inventor supplies and parts, in-house recycling of some materials, patenting information and resources, as well as incubator resources for small startups such as work & meeting spaces, business phone lines, and shipping addresses. Make N Mod will focus on consumers wanting to create, develop, and even sell their products, customers that need access to creative software & hardware tools and equipment, and customers that need resources to run their own business. In the future we will also accommodate consumers that would prefer to create remotely via a computer or personal electronic device and consumers that would use a creation service or purchase an item via kiosks & satellite locations.
